Each upstream section is either a reviewer (ends with `VERDICT:` line: `No Critical/Major`, `Major`, or `Critical`) or an aggregate (carries `**Decision**: pass|repair_needed|...`).

Decide:
  - decision = pass: every upstream section reports clean (No Critical/Major reviewers, or upstream aggregates report pass).
  - decision = repair_needed: at least one upstream finding is Critical or Major (Minor does NOT trigger repair).
  - decision = abort or escalate_human: only when judgment is impossible.

Schema rules you MUST follow:
  - round = {{ round }} (echo exactly).
  - evidence_consumed = exactly this list (no more, no less): {{ expectedEvidenceNodes | dump }}.
  - For decision=repair_needed: blocking_findings is non-empty. Each finding has severity (critical/major/minor), title, evidence_ref, and raised_by must be one id from evidence_consumed.
  - For decision=pass: blocking_findings is empty (or omitted).
  - summary: 1 line for git commit subject. reasoning: 2-5 sentences for audit.

{% if isAggregator %}
Accepted-Minor handling (non_blocking_findings):
  When upstream reviewers raise Minor-severity observations that you
  decide NOT to fix in this ticket (you still pass), surface them as
  non_blocking_findings. Each entry has the same shape as a blocking
  finding (severity, title, evidence_ref, raised_by). Pull from the
  reviewers' "Minor" / "non-blocking" sub-bullets; set severity=minor
  unless the source explicitly said otherwise.

  The runtime will append each entry to the ticket's `# Out of scope`
  section as the durable record of "noted but intentionally not fixed".
  Future agents touching the same file rely on this list — be specific
  and honest. If reviewers found nothing worth recording, leave
  non_blocking_findings empty/omitted.
